main event: Two unidentified objects were reported in the sky over Presque Isle, Maine on September 27, 1968.
interesting points: The report was called in to the Wright-Patterson Air Force Base, but no details of the sighting were provided.
The Air Force later requested the witness to complete an additional form (AF Form 117) to provide more details about the sighting.
The investigation of the case was completed, but the conclusion was that there was 'INSUFFICIENT DATA FOR EVALUATION'.
The letter was signed by Lt. Colonel Hector Quintanilla, Jr., who was the Chief of the Aerial Phenomena Office at the time.
